com.infinityrefactoring.reflections

Class PathExpression

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.infinityrefactoring.reflections.PathExpression
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<ExpressionNode>

    public class PathExpression
extends Object
implements Iterable<ExpressionNode>
    Represents a path expression, that can be used to access nested fields or methods of a given root object. A path expression is compound by a list of expression nodes separated by a dot. Path Expression examples:
    • foo
    • person.name
    • person.name.toLowerCase()
    • bar.getMatrix()[4][6].foo.toString()
    • person.getAddresses()[1].country.name
    Author:
    Thom√°s Sousa Silva (ThomasSousa96)
    See Also:
    compile(String), Reflections, ClassWrapper

      • STATIC_PATH_EXPRESSION_PREFIX

        public static final String STATIC_PATH_EXPRESSION_PREFIX
        The static path expression prefix. A static path must be in the following pattern: "class(the.full.root.class.name)some.non.static.path.expression".

      • concat

        public PathExpression concat(PathExpression pathExpression)
        Concatenates the specified path expression to the end of this path expression. Note: If the given path expression is a static path expression then only the non static part will be concatenated. Examples: 
         "foo".concat("bar") returns "foo.bar"
 "foo".concat("class(com.Bar)name") returns "foo.name"
        Parameters:
        pathExpression - the path expression that is concatenated to the end of this instance.
        Returns:
        a path expression that represents the concatenation of this instance followed by the given path expression.

      • subPath

        public PathExpression subPath(int beginIndex,
                              int endIndex)
        Returns another path expression instance with a nodes amount reduced. Per example: "foo.bar.name".subPath(1, 2) returns "bar".
        Parameters:
        beginIndex - the index of the begin node (inclusive)
        endIndex - the index of the end node (exclusive)
        Returns:
        a another path expression
        Throws:
        IndexOutOfBoundsException - if the index range is invalid
        IllegalArgumentException - if the endIndex is less or equal than the beginIndex
